<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-066-214 </DOCNO><DOCID>11 475 796</DOCID><JOURNAL>ACM Transactions on Database Systems  Sept 1991 v16 n3 p535(29).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>An incremental access method for ViewCache: concept, algorithms,and cost analysis. (Technical)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Roussopoulos, Nicholas.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>An Incremental Access Method (IAM) is presented for theamortization of ViewCache maintenance costs.andP;  Amortization isbased on a deferred update strategy where a ViewCache remainsoutdated until a query needs to materialize the view, prompting anincremental update of the ViewCache.andP;  Conditions are defined underwhich incremental access to ViewCache is cost effective.andP;  The IAMoffers significant performance advantages by utilizing theViewCache storage organization to perform updates and thematerialization of the ViewCaches in an interleaved mode throughthe use of one-pass algorithms.andP;  The incremental access methodoutperforms query modification under favorable conditions.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Cache MemoryAlgorithmsCost Benefit AnalysisData Base Management SystemsAccess MethodsTerminologyQuery Processing.andO;Feature:   illustrationchartgraph.andO;Caption:   Example of a multilevel ViewCache. (chart)Binary ViewCache partitions marked by *. (graph)Optimal ViewCache traversal. (graph)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>